<TEXT>
president carlos menem has 
accepted the credentials of the first british ambassador to 
argentina since the two countries went to war over the falklands in 
1982 
the war is an issue of the past the new ambassador 
humphrey maud told reporters covering the ceremony wednesday at 
the presidents official residence in the suburban town of olivos 
now we can think of the future 
ownership of the falklands is not an issue for discussion at 
this moment said the 56yearold career diplomat 
britains rules the islands off argentinas southern coast but 
argentina claims them 
relations with britain were cut after argentina invaded the 
islands in april 1982 argentina surrendered after 74 days of 
fighting that killed about 1200 people 
relations thawed only after menems inauguration in july 1989 
he proposed that the question of who rules the islands be set aside 
for the immediate future 
</TEXT>
