<TEXT>
nonpolluting 300mileanhour magnetic 
levitating trains could be whisking passengers between some us 
cities before the end of the 1990s the federal railroad 
administrator predicts 
the country may be entering a new era in ground transportation 
with projects already beginning in california nevada and florida 
said gilbert e carmichael who heads the federal railroad 
administration 
several other areas also are looking into magnetic levitation or 
highspeed rail he said 
carmichael in an interview wednesday discussed an fra report 
completed this week that said magnetically levitated trains are 
feasible for the united states even without significant federal 
funding 
no magnetic train yet carries paying passengers anywhere in the 
world but carmichael said he recently rode on a 19mile test 
system in west germany 
you feel it levitate and then you feel it swoosh you along 
without any vibration carmichael said cows were grazing 
underneath when we passed over and they didnt even look up 
because the trains float on a powerful magnetic field there is 
no friction or wear and far less energy is consumed it takes about 
as much electricity to run the german system as to aircondition 
it carmichael said 
fares would be about 20 percent below air fares and on some 
shorter routes 40 percent lower the administrator said 
the report said the united states which started and then 
abandoned the maglev technology two decades ago still could 
create a better system than those being tested in west germany and 
japan the system is intended as an alternative to shortdistance 
air travel 
carmichael said he expects at least two maglev routes to be in 
operation before the end of the decade along with two or three 
highspeed rail systems 
but he said the decision must be made whether to invest 1 
billion to develop a new us system to get into a joint venture 
with a foreign system that already is well along or simply to buy 
either the german or japanese products 
maglev technologies are in competition with highspeed rail 
which is a fast steelonsteel system and with swedish tilting 
trains that allow faster service on existing tracks without 
passengers feeling the curves 
carmichael said all of the systems can be used along with 
tiltrotor aircraft in a multimodal approach to preventing 
transportation gridlock next century 
the fra study said any heavily traveled route of 100 to 500 
miles holds potential for the magnetic system 
a system of up to 2600 miles could be built for about 55 
billion with taxfree bonds and no public financing assuming 
rightsofway are available at little or no cost the report said 
an advisory panel to the senate committee on environment and 
public works recommended a year ago that the government allocate 
750 million over six years to develop test and demonstrate 
several maglev routes 
the federal budget so far calls for only 12 million to further 
study the potential for highspeed trains 
but there are signs of growing support from industry 
on monday a partnership headed by bechtel international inc of 
san francisco put up 500000 for the right to bid on a 5 billion 
maglev train between southern california and las vegas planners 
hope to have the train running in seven years 
business and government leaders in pittsburgh are moving to make 
the city a technological and manufacturing base for the 
germandeveloped maglev system while developing a 19mile 
demonstration run between downtown pittsburgh and the citys 
international airport 
another privately funded project in florida is planning to build 
a 14mile german system by 1994 to link orlando airport to disney 
world and other nearby resorts 
carmichael said at least two companies are bidding to develop a 
highspeed rail system in texas to link houston and dallas 
the fras report envisions five maglev systems that eventually 
could be tied together 
they include a giant web in the northeast running from boston to 
richmond va and going as far west as minneapolis and st louis 
in the south the floating trains would zip from nashville down 
to miami and from charlotte across to birmingham 
the californianevada system eventually would link reno 
sacramento san francisco and san diego to the already planned los 
angeleslas vegas line 
a northwest system would tie portland to seattle and the 
dallashouston line would connect to san antonio and austin 
</TEXT>
