study titled kids clout americans attitudes on childrens 
issues 
the study published by the national association of childrens 
hospitals and related institutions discusses how concern for 
children can influence voting behavior 
the association found 60 percent of americans believe the 
quality of childrens lives has become worse over the past five 
years and more than one american in four believes that it has 
become much worse 
