presidentelect alberto fujimori has named as 
his prime minister a former centerright cabinet minister the 
strongest signal yet that he is indeed embracing the tough 
marketoriented reforms he once eschewed 
fujimori on wednesday night named exagriculture minister juan 
carlos hurtado miller to be his prime minister and economics 
minister 
the presidentelect who takes over from centerleft president 
alan garcia on july 28 said hurtado miller would announce the rest 
of the cabinet this afternoon 
the appointment came two days after two of fujimoris top 
economic advisers resigned the two had supported a gradual 
economic adjustment program 
before the june 10 election fujimori sharply criticized the 
type of marketoriented economic shock therapy advocated by his 
opponent novelist mario vargas llosa 
