<TEXT>
here is a brief description of the leading participants in 
cambodias 11yearold civil war 
the vietnameseinstalled government of premier hun sen 
comprised largely of khmer rouge defectors is fighting a coalition 
of three cambodian resistance groups 
the communist khmer rouge armed by china is the strongest of 
the three its political leader is khieu samphan the khmer rouge 
ruled cambodia in 19751978 during that time hundreds of 
thousands of its 8 million people died from khmer rouge executions 
famine and civil unrest 
knowledgeable sources say the khmer rouge has about 30000 
troops 
the khmer peoples national liberation front is one of two 
noncommunist guerrilla groups it is led by former cambodian prime 
minister son sann it was formed from a number of noncommunist 
groups that had fought the khmer rouge since 1975 
noncommunist followers of former cambodian leader prince 
norodom sihanouk have formed their own force the national sihanouk 
army sihanouk is the also leader of the resistance coalition 
noncommunist resistance forces number an estimated 20000 
the resistance is based along the thai border armed principally 
by china it holds cambodias un seat 
the sovietbacked vietnamese invaded cambodia in late 1978 
ousting the khmer rouge government vietnam announced it had 
removed all its troops from cambodia in september since then the 
resistance has made its biggest gains of the war 
