<TEXT>
here is a chronological look at the cambodian conflict 
on christmas day 1978 tanks rolled from ban me thuot in the 
central highlands to start vietnams invasion of cambodia and war 
with its former communist ally the khmer rouge 
on jan 7 1979 the vietnamese marched into phnom penh so 
unexpectedly swift was the strike that the khmer rouge left behind 
halfeaten meals and tons of arms as they fled 
on jan 10 a new communist government was proclaimed it was 
led by heng samrin and other khmer rouge defectors who had fled to 
vietnam fearing the previous governments bloody purges but 
sanctuary from thailand and arms from china soon raised the khmer 
rouge from its knees into a potent guerrilla insurgency 
in januaryfebruary 1979 china wages a border war against 
vietnam to punish it for the invasion of cambodia 
in june 1982 the khmer rouge the forces of prince norodom 
sihanouk and of former premier son sann form a resistance 
coalition the united nations recognizes it as cambodias 
government 
in march 1985 vietnamese forces allied to the government in 
phnom penh overrun every major border camp in its greatest victory 
of the war against the resistance coalition 
in december 1986 nguyen van linh head of vietnams communist 
party focuses on economic reform and breaking the international 
isolation that the cambodian war has caused 
in july 1987 sihanouk holds peace talks in france with phnom 
penhs prime minister hun sen 
on dec 19 1988 premier li peng says china will decrease its 
aid to the resistance as vietnam withdraws from cambodia he said 
china will halt all aid when the troops are gone 
in december 1988 vietnam begins its pullout of 50000 troops 
in january 1989 vietnam sends a senior official to beijing to 
discuss the conflict the two sides agree that vietnam will 
withdraw its troops by september in exchange for an end to chinese 
aid to the guerrillas 
in july 1989 a 19nation conference on cambodia opens in 
paris sihanouk calls for interim government with khmer rouge 
participation hun sen strongly opposes the idea 
in september 1989 vietnam says it has withdrawn its last 
troops guerrillas call it a sham and begin a general offensive 
china calls the pullout a fraud and indicates it will continue 
arming the guerrillas until there is a political settlement 
on sept 30 1989 noncommunist guerrillas seize the district 
seat of thmar puok near thai border they make their greatest gains 
in the war in the coming months 
on feb 1113 1990 the un security council permanent 
members meeting in new york say regrouping the cambodian armies 
into designated areas is essential to the peace process but they 
fail to agree on proposals to disarm the factions 
in february sihanouk and hun sen hold talks in bangkok 
thailand they agree on the need for a un presence in cambodia 
and a supreme national body 
in april sihanouk urges an immediate ceasefire in his 
country he says the un security council should deploy 
peacekeeping troops to enforce it 
in june cambodian guerrillas launch major attacks and seize 
areas of several provinces as cambodias warring factions prepare 
to meet to discuss a ceasefire chinese thai and us officials 
join attempts to foster progress in peace talks stalled by the 
khmer rouge refusal to attend 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

