baath party and the 10man revolutionary command council headed by 
saddam 
saddam exercises neartotal rule over iraqs 17 million people 
through his vast security apparatus the inner circle of iraqs 
leadership is packed with saddams relatives by blood or marriage 
from his extended clan from takrit in northern iraq 
the baath party is ostensibly socialist and panarab but is now 
virtually devoid of any ideology beyond saddams policies 
saddam has turned his reign into a personality cult that has 
