ralph nader argued that wealthy investors used federal protection 
for up to 100000 in deposits to reap substantial interest income 
now that scores of sampls have gone under poor and middle class 
taxpayers are unfairly being asked to pay he said 
kennedy proposed legislation that would raise 100 billion in 
bailout costs over five years by imposing three new taxes a 75 
percent surtax on interest dividends and capital gains for 
individuals reporting income more than 100000 per year a 5 
percent surtax on corporations earning more than 75000 per year 
and elimination of an inheritance tax provision that forgives taxes 
on appreciated capital gains at death 
