the national media president nixon managed to lead america out of 
the vietnam war and bring back our pows 
before the ceremony in the cool of the library nixon was asked 
how he felt 
i feel as good as the rest of them look nixon said pointing 
to his fellow presidents 
nixon toured the library wednesday for the first time and was 
asked how he liked it 
what ive seen of it ive been impressed but im not the best 
judge he conceded im going to let these three be the judge 
and jury im glad to be in the hands of this jury 
ford already has a library in michigan reagan will open his in 
simi valley 60 miles to the northwest of nixons next february 
and plans already are under way for one to house bushs papers and 
artifacts 
nixons library is more of a museum since it houses none of 
nixons papers next year if plans are followed the library will 
get nixons archives from his congressional and vice presidential 
days and those that followed his presidency but the real 
presidential papers 42 million pages of documents are in a 
warehouse in alexandria va 
the nixon papers were seized by congress after he left office to 
prevent him from destroying any watergate documents 
millions of pages have been opened for perusal by scholars and 
the library will play tapes of 33 conversations that nixon recorded 
secretly but nearly 4000 hours more of tapes as well as 15000 
important documents have been withheld from the public through 
actions by nixons lawyers 
