the house ethics committee voted without 
dissent thursday to recommend a reprimand of rep barney frank 
dmass for his relationship with male prostitute stephen gobie 
according to sources familiar with the closeddoor deliberations 
the reprimand would be a more severe sanction against frank than 
democrats on the 12member panel had been advocating 
thats what people in the house were sort of expecting would 
happen said one source 
the committee was concerned not only with franks sexual 
relationship to gobie but with actions he took on gobies behalf 
committee members refused to discuss the case and frank refused 
to comment one member rep larry craig ridaho was back in his 
