whether he had voted by proxy 
the committee hurriedly left its meeting room after more than 
two hours of discussion members all but ignored reporters waiting 
outside 
the committee is adjourned i have no statement said rep 
julian dixon dcalif the committee chairman 
the committee which has been looking into the frank case for 10 
months scheduled no new meetings 
among matters of concern to the committee were the fact that 
frank wrote favorable letters on his congressional letterhead to 
court officials who were supervising gobies probation on several 
felony convictions he also invoked congressional privilege to 
waive parking tickets incurred by gobie while using franks car 
frank said he only sought to have the tickets waived when gobie 
was using the car for official business 
the recommendation would have to be voted on by the house 
reprimand is a relatively new punishment having been used against 
six members since 1976 and simply consists of a vote to accept the 
committee report 
the committee could have recommended the more severe censure 
used before 1976 in which the member must stand before his 
colleagues as a resolution condemning his behavior is read or it 
could have recommended expulsion which no one expected 
first word of the committees decision was broadcast by cbs and 
nbc in their evening news programs 
the house committees action comes a day after its senate 
counterpart recommended that the senate denounce sen dave 
durenberger rminn for financial misconduct and require him to 
pay 124000 to the senate or to charities as restitution 
the case has been one of the most difficult ever considered by 
the ethics panel because what it dealt with was personal behavior 
rather than official duties conservatives on the 12member panel 
have been holding out for a strong punishment which would involve 
a vote by the full house criticizing franks behavior 
when the case first became public late last summer frank 
admitted that he paid gobie 80 for sex in 1985 and then hired him 
as a housekeeper and driver with personal funds 
he said he fired gobie in august 1987 after learning that gobie 
was running a prostitution ring out of franks capitol hill 
apartment 
frank has repeatedly denied gobies allegation that he was aware 
of the prostitution long before he ended the relationship 
in past cases the committee has voted and not released the 
decision for a day or two dixon touched off speculation that the 
panel may have done just that thursday when he said without being 
asked that he would not comment on any votes the committee may or 
may not have taken but neither dixon nor other members would 
discuss the deliberations 
