word from any committee member on thursdays meeting he declined 
to discuss the committee deliberations and said he had no idea when 
the panel planned to meet again 
i have gotten no word official or unofficial frank said 
the committee made up of six democrats and six republicans had 
been deadlocked on the severity of punishment frank should receive 
democrats reportedly wanted to issue a letter of reproval one of 
the mildest sanctions possible because it would not require a vote 
of the full house on franks conduct republican committee members 
had pushed for a tougher sanction 
rep william dannemeyer rcalif has said he would seek a vote 
to expel frank if the ethics committee sought a lesser sanction 
