broad concessions won by the the strikers included a promise by 
the government of president violeta barrios de chamorro not to fire 
those taking part in the walkout 
clashes during the strike between heavily armed sandinistas and 
government supporters killed at least six people and wounded more 
than 100 
ortega warned government officials to proceed with caution 
because they are provoking more conflicts 
now we have to defend democracy against those who want to 
return to somocism he said adding that extremists within the 
government want to see our heads rolls but if any heads roll it 
will be theirs 
the chamorro government which ended a decade of sandinista rule 
april 25 declared thursday a national holiday but did not hold 
public celebrations 
mrs chamorro accused the sandinistas of trying to restore a 
dictatorship she said in a televised speech wednesday night that 
all nicaraguans had supported the revolution of july 19 1979 
because we all believed that we were breaking the gate of a 
tyranny to enter the promised land of democracy and freedom 
unfortunately the revolution was confiscated by an exclusive 
party with a totalitarian ideology it had kept hidden instead of 
democracy dictatorship rose again like a cadaver 
sandinista supporters shooting machine guns and other weapons 
into the air cruised managua streets at dawn thursday to kick off 
the festivities and shouted the newest sandinista slogan the 
revolution continues not one step back 
in an apparent attempt to draw people away from the sandinista 
rally nicaraguas only tv station governmentrun channel 6 
scheduled backtoback movies all day including batman the 
fly and crocodile dundee 
but neither movies nor rain kept away the crowds estimated by 
reporters at about 40000 half the attendance projected by 
sandinista officials 
last years july 19th sandinista rally drew about 100000 
people but many were government workers compelled to attend or 
risk losing their job 
mrs chamorro said bad nicaraguans want this july 19 not 
to signify democracy but military dictatorship again and asked 
the people to support her 
i want to teach those who only know violence the benefits of 
respecting legal rights and of brotherly love 
managua residents awakened to the sounds of fire from machine 
guns pistols and ak47s in nearly every neighborhood 
the noise smacked of the day 11 years ago when sandinista 
leaders and others who fought dictator anastasio somoza rode 
triumphant into managua to celebrate the secret flight two days 
earlier of the last of the somozas 
chamorro supporters say the president should have taken a 
tougher stance with the strikers and mrs chamorro alluded to that 
in her speech 
it is difficult to educate those who have been fanaticized by 
violence and terror she said we carry an inheritance of 
barbarian aggression that almost destroyed managua in a few hours 
but we must prove to them the value of peace and the 
wellbeing that freedom brings and the greatness we can achieve 
working together as brothers 
mrs chamorro was on the original fivemember sandinista junta 
she is the most prominent of those nicaraguans who backed the 
sandinistas in their early years but became disenchanted 
 
</TEXT>
