<TEXT>
president roh taewoo called on friday 
for an end to cold war on the korean peninsula and proposed 
unrestricted travel between communist north korea and south korea 
the time has come to end total division roh said in a major 
nationwide radio and television broadcast korea must not remain 
the worlds only land still partitioned by cold war politics 
there was no immediate reaction from north korea acceptance by 
north korea would open the peninsula for the first time since 1945 
and set the stage for national unification 
roh noted in the speech that president kim il sung of north 
korea proposed conditional free travel on jan 1 and said i am 
convinced there will be no obstacle 
roh said south korea would open its border at panmunjom in the 
demilitarized zone for five days as of aug 13 and accept 
breathren from the north without restrictions 
roh said north koreans would be allowed to freely visit any 
place in the south and meet anyone they want he challenged north 
korea to offer the same provisions to south koreans 
he said that in the near future foreigners would be 
permitted to freely travel across the border a move which might 
allow tourists and could be expected to speed up the easing of 
tensions between the koreas 
a tide of openness and reconciliation has torn away the iron 
curtain separating the east and the west and is now shaping a new 
world in which nations are cooperating with each other regardless 
of differences in ideology and political systems he said 
even if north korea cannot agree to mutual exchanges at this 
time for some unavoidable reason we will onesidely open our 
society competely roh declared 
south koreans reacted by welcoming the presidents announcement 
but many doubted totalitarian north korea one of the last 
remaining closed societies would allow its citizens to visit the 
south 
the united national movement for democracy south koreas 
largest dissident group called the border proposal a step 
forward it also demanded the immediate release of political 
prisoners in south korea including a student and pastor jailed for 
travel to north korea 
rohs cabinet will meet saturday to review proceedures for 
allowing travel to take place south korean law now makes it a 
violation of national security to visit north korea without 
government permission which has been rarely given 
the korean peninsula was divided into communist north and 
capitalist south in 1945 at the end of world war ii the two fought 
a bitter threeyear civil and ideological war in the early 1950s 
and have remained hostile 
the fact that compatriots in the south and north are still 
unable to visit each other is a shame on us who are a proud people 
with a rich cultural heritage that has evolved over many 
millenniums such a state of affairs should not continue any 
longer he said 
both north and south korea have talked about free travel but 
have never negotiated it the border has remained tightly closed to 
virtually all travel mail and telephone communication for more 
than four decades 
two weeks ago north korea announced it would open a portion of 
its border for restricted passage within a small border area 
beginning aug 15 
the korean peninsula was freed from 35 years of japanese 
colonial rule on aug 15 1945 and the day is historically 
symbolic to both koreas 
the proposal by both koreas calls for the border to be opened at 
panmunjom the truce village in the demilitarized zone that divides 
the peninsula in half panmunjom about 35 miles north of seoul is 
the site of periodic northsouth talks 
panmunjom is inaccessible to the average korean citizen from 
either side the border between the koreas is the most heavily 
fortified in the world with more than 1 million armed soldiers 
behind concrete bunkers and barbed wire 
the southern half of the panmunjom area is guarded by the 
usled united nations command the command has said that it would 
honor the wishes of the koreans regarding a border opening 
in 1985 the koreas exchanged 151 citizens from both sides for a 
fourday family exchange but the visits were limited to the 
capitals of the two nations 
the two koreas are to sign an agreement july 26 setting a date 
for their first prime ministers talks expected to be held in seoul 
in september 
consider how magnificent and great an age the 21st century 
could be for our people if only the country is unified and the 70 
million korans become one again the president said 
south korea has about 43 million residents while north korea 
has a population of about 22 million people 
</TEXT>
