the queen told the 2000 parading veterans some in wheelchairs 
pushed by young paratroopers 
the main anniversary celebrations were held in late may 
climaxing with a ragtag flotilla of 50 vessels making their way 
across the english channel from the french port of dunkirk to 
ramsgate england 
over 10 days in may and june 1940 british dutch french and 
belgian warships and civilian craft evacuated 338000 british 
french and belgian troops from dunkirk which was surrounded after 
the germans broke through across northern france 
those saved amid the bombs and gunfire helped form the nucleus 
of the victorious allied armies which invaded normandy in june 1944 
for morale purposes prime minister sir winston churchill 
ordered the dunkirk defeat to be announced as a deliverance and it 
has since been regarded in britain as something of a miracle 
