tissue samples for tests drew fire from some environmentalists 
critics said the endangered mammals should be tested to see if they 
ingested oil from the exxon valdez oil spill in nearby prince 
william sound 
we have no reason to think at this point that its anything 
other than natural mortality steve zimmerman of the fisheries 
service said tuesday from juneau 
he noted the whales had migrated several thousand miles from 
their feeding area in the bering sea to the mexican coast last 
fall then returned 
any that are physiologically weak are going to have problems 
toward the end of that long migration he said 
he said the number of fatalities was high but the whales could 
have died of old age parasites genetic defects marginal feeding 
and exhaustion among other possibilities 
environmentalists have expressed concern because gray whales 
feed on the oceans bottom where weathered oil would sink and 
accumulate in sediments 
