<TEXT>
joe slovo lionized by blacks 
and vilified by whites is a lifelong revolutionary who leads one 
of the few communist movements still in ascendancy 
slovo the mildmannered white lawyer was on the african national 
congress team that met with the white national party government in 
talks between south africas two most powerful political forces 
the other joe slovo who angers whites and is an idol to young 
blacks is general secretary of the south african communist party 
and former head of the anc guerrilla campaign 
by marking me out as enemy no 1 he said in an interview 
the government has endeared me in the hearts of most people in 
this country at 64 slovo looks more like a favorite uncle than 
a leader of revolution 
he is goodhumored engaging and slightly rumpled with bushy 
eyebrows thick glasses that slide down his nose a full head of 
gray hair and a gravel voice from heavy smoking 
slovo fled south africa in 1963 and returned in april wearing a 
dark blue suit loud floral tie cherry red socks and a wide smile 
as i was saying before i was so rudely interrupted 27 years 
ago he said at an airport news conference we are really on 
our way 
nelson mandela said slovo was the primary african national 
congress speaker on most major issues discussed with the government 
in may slovo probably will play a similar role in any future 
negotiations on ending apartheid 
however easygoing the exterior he is a dedicated revolutionary 
who became a communist party member at age 15 slovos parents 
immigrated from lithuania 
he does not apologize for his years as leader of an anc bombing 
and sabotage campaign that caused hundreds of deaths and injuries 
mostly to blacks 
his wife and fellow communist ruth first was killed by a 
parcel bomb in neighboring mozambique in 1982 slovo says that 
south african agents were responsible and that he also has been a 
target 
what sustained me was the certainty that i would come back 
slovo said of his long exile i never doubted that for one 
moment 
in 1987 he gave up leadership of the ancs armed wing to 
concentrate on the communist party he remains on the anc 
policymaking body the national executive committee 
the anc and south african communist party have been allies since 
the 1920s and slovo is one of several people who holds posts in 
both 
an angry reader wrote in the citizen a conservative newspaper 
he and his ilk have destroyed the peace of south africa red joe 
should never have come back 
former president pw botha cited the governments decision to 
allow slovos return as one reason he quit the national party after 
more than 50 years 
at rallies in black townships chants of viva nelson mandela 
viva often are followed by cries of viva joe slovo viva 
the red flag of the communist party invaribly hangs beside the 
green gold and black of the anc at such rallies 
south africa seems to be one of the last places on earth where 
the display of the hammer and sickle at public rallies still evokes 
cheers herman nickel a former us ambassador to south africa 
wrote in the wall street journal 
many blacks equate apartheid with capitalism and are drawn to 
the socialist economics of the communist party but young blacks in 
particular have little formal understanding of either system 
the south african communist party was founded in 1921 and banned 
in 1950 secrecy about policies and membership makes its strength 
hard to measure but its key role in the anc is unquestioned and 
the communists also are considered influential in the trade union 
movement 
president fw de klerk legalized the party in february along 
with other antiapartheid groups slovo said he remains convinced 
socialism can succeed in south africa despite the collapse of 
communist governments in eastern europe 
perhaps the reason they changed their names and their 
leadership and their policies is because they have a past to be 
ashamed of he said of the east european communists i dont 
think we have 
nonetheless the south african communists have moderated their 
positions after decades of loyalty to the soviet unions communist 
party 
slovo calls for a multiparty democracy and says transition from 
capitalism to a socialist state would be a longterm process 
pursued peacefully 
many white south africans still suspect the worst of the 
communists however 
ken owen editor of financial daily business day wrote 
behind the smiling mask lies an organization that thrives on 
secrecy totalitarian driven by fascist instincts undemocratic 
manipulative 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

