for his part greenspan told members of the senate banking 
committee i can only offer the assurance that the federal 
reserve will act as it has in the past to endeavor to keep the 
economic expansion on track 
his statements came as part of his midyear report on the state 
of the economy 
in its economic outlook the fed said it expected the economy to 
grow at a modest rate of between 175 percent and 25 percent in 
1991 lower than the administrations forecast monday of 29 
percent growth 
in assessing current developments greenspan said the country 
had an economy which is not on the edge of either falling apart 
into a recession or about to take on highly inflationary 
characteristics 
