73 cents per share up 11 percent from 3161 million or 73 cents 
per share in the second quarter of 1989 
revenue fell to 606 billion from 636 billion a year earlier 
reflecting a drop in shearsons revenue to 262 billion from 329 
billion 
american express said its results reflected the costs of 
purchasing 750 million in preferred stock from shearson at the end 
of the first quarter 
american express which currently owns about 60 percent of 
shearson plans to take full control of its subsidiary and issue 
254 million new shares to finance the transaction stockholders 
will vote on the plan next month 
shearson reported 51 million in earnings down from 55 million 
a year earlier american express said its share of shearsons 
earnings was 265 million down from 338 million last year 
american express has pumped 1 billion in capital into the 
struggling division in recent months and ordered a restructuring 
that included about 2000 layoffs shearson is reorganizing its 
corporate structure combining four divisions into two and plans to 
rename itself shearson lehman brothers inc 
american express standout division in the second quarter was 
its travel related services division which includes the firms 
charge card and travelers check business the division posted a 
163 percent rise in earnings to 2492 million from 2142 
million a year earlier 
