requirements 
chicagobased stotler group a publicly traded company 
confirmed in the announcement that stotler and co had brought 
itself into compliance with the capital requirements 
the developments mean stotler could avert a cashflow crisis and 
will avoid restrictions on its brokerage operations while sparing 
mahlmann further embarrassment 
the statement said the offer announced thursday was subject to 
approval by the investors board of directors the deal will die if 
such approval is not granted by 11 am edt monday stotler group 
said 
stotler group confirmed wednesdays board of trade announcement 
that it had brought itself into compliance with a commodity futures 
trading commission rule requiring futures brokerages to maintain in 
a separate account liquid assets equal to 4 percent of customer 
funds 
on wednesday after a deadline set by the board of trade had 
passed the exchange released a statement saying it believes the 
firm has achieved the requisite capital requirements 
the exchange had ordered stotler to boost its capital or face 
restrictions on its trading activities the exchange can force a 
brokerage out of the business of trading for customers if its 
capital level falls below 4 percent of customer funds 
stotlers plan for bringing its capital level into compliance 
included trimming it customer base and finding an investor 
stotler group had said that without new capital from an outside 
source it might have trouble meeting its debt obligations 
stotler is one of the countrys 10 largest commodity brokerages 
with its roots in the grain business the company also trades 
financial futures which have outstripped agricultural commodities 
in trading volume in recent years 
