san jose calif car and truck plant during the boom years of the 
mid1980s ford paid overtime to keep the cars and trucks rolling 
out of existing plants 
the average wage for an assembly worker at the big three is just 
less than 15 an hour before overtime or benefits 
in addition to curbing overtime and protecting current jobs the 
union will seek higher wage and improved pensions more management 
accountability and protection of healthcare benefits 
the companies will be looking for more flexibility in work rules 
and scheduling and ways to hold down soaring health costs 
