a former citibank vice president whose job was 
to safeguard assets was sentenced thursday to eight years in prison 
for embezzling securities worth 25 million from the banks vault 
of the five 5 million certificates stolen four were recovered 
when the defendant mario rios pinochet tried to negotiate them 
three days after the jan 25 theft prosecutors said 
the fifth certificate which matured in february was never 
recovered 
pinochet 48 of weston conn claims to be a distant relative 
of former chilean dictator augusto pinochet 
he was convicted in may by a manhattan federal court jury of 
four felony counts stemming from the embezzlement 
pinochet was fired by citibank after his feb 1 arrest he 
maintains his innocence and plans an appeal 
even if it takes me 50 years i am going to prove i am 
innocent he told us district judge robert ward 
wards sentence of eight years fell in the middle range of the 
punishment allowed by federal sentencing guidelines the judge said 
he considered the seriousness of the charges and pinochets lack of 
remorse 
there is no question that his position allowed him to commit 
the crime ward said 
pinochet was a vice president in charge of a risk management 
team that investigated discrepancies in the handling of 
multimilliondollar securities held by citibank 
bank employees testified at trial that the bearer securities 
disappeared while pinochet was conducting a count of commercial 
paper in the banks vault under the guise of trying to improve 
procedures to safeguard assets 
then in what ward described as a james bond scenario he 
arranged the delivery of four of the certificates to the stamford 
conn office of paine webber inc in an envelope taped to the 
inside of a chilean newspaper 
according to trial evidence pinochet said he received the 
certificates from a courier in chile on behalf of three principals 
who turned out to be fictitious 
he instructed a broker at paine webber to wire the proceeds to 
an account in bermuda but the transaction was never completed 
because the broker discovered that the securities had been reported 
missing by citibank 
ward also imposed three years probation but ordered no fine 
because pinochet who is married with three children has no money 
the judge said pinochet would have to pay restitution if 
citibank is held responsible for the missing 5 million certificate 
during the years of his imprisonment and probation 
pinochet who has been in jail since his arrest was denied a 
request to be freed pending his appeal 
