pacific telesis based in san francisco said it earned 287 
million or 72 cents a share in the quarter ended june 30 down 
from 325 million or 79 cents a share in 1989s second quarter 
revenue totaled 243 billion up from 241 billion 
the company blamed the lower results on a rate reduction 
associated with telephone regulation restructuring in california 
and increased expenses for network and operating improvements 
for the first six months of the year pactel earned 549 
million or 137 a share down from 642 million or 155 a 
