southwestern bell corp reported earnings of 2625 million or 
87 cents a share compared with 2615 million or 87 cents a 
share for the same period a year earlier revenue totaled 217 
billion up from 214 billion 
the st louisbased company said state and federal telephone 
rate reductions offset growth in new service 
the company said earnings in 1989s second quarter were swollen 
by a onetime 118 million gain from a phone routing change if 
that gain were excluded southwesterns profit would have risen 44 
percent in this years second quarter 
