<TEXT>
ford motor co said thursday it is recalling 
about 110000 1989 and 1990 e and fseries vans and pickup trucks 
with automatic transmissions that might slip out of park 
ford said 103457 of the vehicles are in the united states 
6163 are in canada and 297 are in other countries owners will be 
notified by mail to bring the cars to dealers the company said 
dealers will inspect the vehicles and if necessary replace 
free a snap ring in the transmission with an improved part a 
broken snap ring can prevent the park mechanism from engaging 
ford has received about 100 complaints about the problem none 
involving accidents or injuries spokesman jim trainor said 
trainor said about 90 percent involved the eseries vehicles 
econoline vans usually used as urban delivery trucks or shuttle 
vehicles the rest involved fseries pickup trucks the affected 
vehicles are twowheel drive 
</TEXT>
