frozen pork bellies settled 2 cents lower across the board with 
the contract for delivery in july at 4650 cents a pound and the 
more heavily traded august contract at 4442 cents a pound 
weak consumer demand for bacon which is made from pork bellies 
has weighed on the market for several weeks the situation has been 
reflected in the narrowing gap between prices of fresh bellies on 
the cash market and frozen bellies on the futures market 
belly futures normally are priced about 5 cents below cash 
bellies in midsummer creating an incentive for belly slicers to 
take bellies out of cold storage to meet the traditional summer 
surge in bacon demand said thomas morgan president of sterling 
research corp in arlington heights ill 
but so far this month bacon demand has been so weak and 
supplies of fresh bellies so ample that cash prices have dropped 
below futures on thursday fresh bellies sold for as low as 43 
cents a pound compared with the low of 4442 cents for the august 
futures contract 
the demand is slow enough that theyre barely using the fresh 
bellies so theres no incentive for them to pull the bellies out 
of the freezer said paul georgy president of the futures 
brokerage allendale inc in crystal lake ill 
