securities and exchange commission chairman 
richard c breeden wound up defending rival regulator wendy gramm 
thursday to a senate panel questioning white house commitment to 
legislation that would shift regulatory control of stock index 
futures 
breeden also suggested a cap on the deposit insurance system and 
said a tax on stock transactions could hurt the markets 
but the senate banking committee hearing on modernizing 
financial institutions shifted to pending legislation on stock 
index futures as several panel members expressed doubts that the 
