the legislation would strip the commodity futures trading 
commission of authority over stock index futures and transfer it to 
the sec 
stock index futures often used in program trading strategies by 
large institutional investors such as pension funds allow 
investors to trade on the movement of a basket of stocks without 
having to buy the underlying stocks 
breeden and treasury secretary nicholas brady say the sec should 
have control over stock index futures to curb extreme volatility 
but wendy gramm the cftc chairman as well as futures exchanges 
and cftc supporters on congressional agriculture committees claim 
the jurisdiction switch isnt necessary and in fact would hurt the 
futures markets 
