futures bill although he said he was encouraged by the number of 
senators at the hearing who expressed a need for reform 
in his testimony breeden outlined possible reforms of deposit 
insurance which many fear could be subject to losses similar to 
those incurred in the multibillion dollar savings and loan bailout 
he suggested a possible cap on deposit insurance which now 
guarantees deposits of up to 100000 in every account 
breeden said the cap could limit the amount of deposits insured 
in each account or limit the number of accounts an individual can 
have insured 
he also suggested a system in which consumers would determine 
how much deposit insurance they want and pay accordingly much like 
life insurance 
i think most taxpayers are showing signs of being irate at 
having to pay for the losses the savings and loans incurred i 
think there will be very strong public support for trimming deposit 
insurance so that the thrift nightmare cannot be repeated 
breeden told reporters 
