<TEXT>
iraqs parliament has proposed that 
president saddam hussein be president for life the official iraqi 
news agency said thursday 
the 250member assembly which has been dominated by the 
governing baath party for the last two decades on wednesday ended 
a special threeday session to debate the new constitution 
ina said the assembly proposed changing a new draft constitution 
that said presidential elections should be held for the first time 
since iraq became a republic in 1958 with the head of state 
serving an eightyear term 
saddam 54 has said he will run in the election but so far 
there has been no mention of any challengers 
that was part of a package of political reforms including a 
multiparty system and a free press saddam promised following the 
august 1988 ceasefire in iraqs eightyear war with iran 
these were widely seen as being little more than a nod toward 
democracy with saddam staying firmly entrenched in power in this 
middle east nation of 17 million people 
saddam has been in absolute control since july 1979 when he 
took over as president from gen ahmed al bakr he served as vice 
president under bakr for 10 years and in effect became the 
strongman of the baathist regime 
ina said the assembly proposed other changes in the draft 
constitution but only mentioned the proposal to make saddam 
president for life 
under the present constitution the president is elected by the 
revolutionary command council composed of senior baath figures 
it will replace the current constitution drawn up in 1968 when 
the baath party seized power in a coup iraqs estimated 8 million 
eligible voters will decide on the new constitution in a nationwide 
referendum later this year 
if saddam is elected president for life presumably by the 
revolutionary command council it will consolidate his rule over 
iraq through his vast security apparatus 
the inner circle of the leadership is packed with saddams 
relatives by blood or marriage from his extended clan from takrit 
in northern iraq 
during the persian gulf war saddam made his power absolute by 
imposing tight personal control of the 1 millionstrong military 
and the baath party ostensibly socialist and panarab but now 
almost devoid of ideology beyond saddams policies 
he has turned his hold on power into a personality cult photos 
and posters of saddam are everywhere it is a capital offense to 
insult him publicly 
iraqi dissident sources speaking on condition of anonymity 
have claimed in recent weeks that up to 40 senior military figures 
including a cousin of saddam were arrested and probably executed 
in saddams latest purge 
there has been no independent confirmation of the reports 
since the ceasefire saddam has revived his ambitions to become 
the paramount leader of the arab world and has built up an arsenal 
of longrange missiles and chemical weapons that has drawn 
denunciations from the west and israel 
the presidentforlife move was reported after saddam earlier 
this week accused kuwait and the united arab emirates of violating 
their opec oil production quotas and threatened to retaliate with 
force if necessary 
he blamed them for an oil glut that drove down prices that he 
claimed has cost iraq 14 billion in lost revenue in the last year 
</TEXT>
